short_description: Multiple firewall reboot alerts observed in SolarWinds
description:
At 17:04, NOC received below firewall reboot alerts in SolarWinds:
 
 "This alert is triggered when there is a change to the "Last Boot" time on the device, indicating a reboot.
 
 If there is no active change, please escalate to the on-call for the device to assess impact.
 
 This alert will need to be manually cleared from the SolarWinds alert page.
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert Br-int-fw-2
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert New-Br-ext-fw-2
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert New-Lv-ext-fw-2
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert New-Br-ext-fw-1
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert New-Lv-ext-fw-1
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert CLRWATER-FW2
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert Br-int-fw-1
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert LSANCA-INETX-FW
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert CLRWATER-FW1
 
 Firwall Rebooted Alert NEW-RCMNCA-INET-FW"
 
 
 
 Note: PRTG did not show any related logs or down alerts, only SolarWinds alerted. Sean was available in teams and he confirmed that although an SSH rule was removed under an approved CHG0155331, the firewalls have not rebooted and had been up for 258 days. Since all firewalls were operational, no reboot was confirmed and no impact so problem was not raised. This INC6052227 was created for tracking.

short_description: BGP Peer 10.10.12.50 - AWS TGW on LV-WAG-RT-B vrf CSP flapping in PRTG
description:
NOC observed that the BGP Peer 10.10.12.50 – AWS TGW on LV-WAG-RT-B (VRF: CSP) triggered an alert at 02:37 PST and cleared at 02:48 PST. It retriggered again at 02:51 PST and cleared at 02:54 PST.
 
 
 
 Issue - BGP Peer 10.10.12.50 – AWS TGW on LV-WAG-RT-B vrf CSP Flapping on PRTG 
 
 Flapped Timings - 11/21/2025 02:37 PST - 02:48 PST and 02:51 PST - 02:54 PST
close_notes:
this looks to be due to AWS maintenance.
 
 
 
 
 
 "Planned maintenance has been scheduled on an AWS Direct Connect endpoint in Switch SUPERNAP 8, Las Vegas, NV from Fri, 21 Nov 2025 10:00:00 GMT to Fri, 21 Nov 2025 14:00:00 GMT for 4 hours. During this maintenance window, your AWS Direct Connect services listed below may become unavailable. 
 
 
 
 dxvif-ffy3c3vv 
 
 dxcon-fgnql9di 
 
 
 
 This maintenance is scheduled to avoid disrupting redundant connections at the same time. "

short_description: Ontario Spectrum Gateway Alerting in PRTG
description:
NOC received Ontario Spectrum Gateway alert in PRTG
 
 
 
 Issue: Ontario Spectrum Gateway (PING) alerting down in PRTG.
 
 Error: Request timed out (ICMP error # 11010)
 
 
 
 NOTE: No abnormalities found in SW. The circuit is UP and running.
close_notes:
This was removed as the new circuit has been up since October 2025.
 
 
 
 Per Raul:
 
 The sensor that is alerting is for the old Spectrum circuit (76.80.221.97). This sensor should have been deleted as part of CHG0153225 when we turned up the new circuit.

short_description: Network - Br-int-fw-1 - ethernet1/9 interface is down
description:
NOC received an alert for Br-int-fw-1 that ethernet1/9 interface was down. Escalated to network engineer on-call.
 
 This is the only interface down on that device.
close_notes: Data Center Personnel Alfred Fuentes swapped out bad SFP transceiver with a new 10GBASE-SRL SFP transceiver. Network Engineering personnel Raul Camacho validated that the port was not operational. No further actions to report. Per ITASK0287231
